#Text=Edward Somerset , 4th Earl of Worcester
#Text=Quartered arms of Sir Edward Somerset , 4th Earl of Worcester , KG
#Text=Edward Somerset , 4th Earl of Worcester , KG , Earl Marshal ( c. 1550 – 3 March 1628 ) was an English aristocrat . [ 1 ]
#Text=He was an important advisor to King James I ( James VI of Scots ) , serving as Lord Privy Seal .
#Text=He was the only son of three children born to the 3rd Earl of Worcester and Christiana North .
#Text=On 21 February 1589 , he succeeded his father as Earl of Worcester .

#Text=In June 1590 Worcester travelled to Edinburgh to congratulate James VI of Scotland on his safe return from Denmark and marriage to Anne of Denmark , and gave notice that the king was to join the Order of the Garter . [ 2 ]
#Text=He discussed with James rumours that English ships had lain in wait for his return .
#Text=At first , he was not able to see Anne of Denmark who had toothache , and he joked that in England this would be interpreted as a sign she was pregnant .
#Text=Worcester had an audience with Anne , and took her letter to Elizabeth .
#Text=He was accompanied by Lord Compton who watched ' pastimes ' or hunting on the sands of Leith . [ 3 ]
#Text=In 1593 he was made a Knight of the Garter .
#Text=In 1606 he was appointed Keeper of the Great Park , a park created for hunting by Henry VIII around Nonsuch Palace , of which Worcester Park was a part .
#Text=The residence Worcester Park House was built in 1607 .
#Text=Family
#Text=He married Lady Elizabeth Hastings in December 1571 .
#Text=She was a daughter of Francis Hastings , 2nd Earl of Huntingdon and Catherine Pole .
#Text=Catherine was a daughter of Henry Pole , 1st Baron Montagu and Jane Neville .
#Text=Jane was in turn a daughter of George Nevill , 4th Baron Bergavenny and his wife Margaret , daughter of Hugh Fenn .
#Text=They had fifteen children among whom were :
#Text=Henry Somerset , 5th Earl of Worcester , his heir and successor , who was later created the 1st Marquess of Worcester ;

#Text=Thomas Somerset , 1st Viscount Somerset ( Peerage of Ireland ) , who was born in 1579 , [ 4 ] died in 1649 ; he was created Viscount Somerset on 8 December 1626 ; in 1616 he married Helen Barry – her third marriage - , with whom he had one daughter :
#Text=Elizabeth Somerset , who might have died young , but that is unsure ;
#Text=Lady Catherine or Katherine Somerset , who died on 6 November 1654 and , before 14 January 1607 , married Thomas Windsor , 6th Baron Windsor , with whom she had no issue ; and

#Text=Lady Blanche Somerset , who died 28 October 1649 , and married Thomas Arundell , 2nd Baron Arundell of Wardour , with whom she had one son and two daughters , his only children ; the settlement for this marriage was on 11 May 1607 .
#Text=Lady Frances Somerset , wife of William Morgan , esquire of Llantarnam [ 5 ] and mother of Edward Morgan ( c. 1612 – 24 June 1653 ) , who was the great-great grandfather of Daniel Boone .
#Text=Sir Charles Somerset ( 1587/8 – 1665 ) , traveller and writer , Knight of the Bath . [ 4 ]
#Text=Lady Elizabeth Somerset , married Sir Henry Guildford .
#Text=Lady Katherine Somerset ( 1575-1624 ) , married William Petre , 2nd Baron Petre .

#Text=Four of his daughters danced as the rivers of Monmouthshire in the court masque Tethys ' Festival on 5 June 1610 ; Lady Catherine Windsor as the " Nymph of Usk " ; Lady Katherine Petre as the " Nymph of Olwy " ; Lady Elizabeth Guildford as the " Nymph of Dulesse " ; and Lady Mary Wintour as the " Nymph of Wye " . [ 6 ]
#Text=Somerset is buried in the family chapel in the Church of St Cadoc , Raglan , Monmouthshire [ 7 ]
#Text=Ancestry
